<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1272,1570]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis box="[198,301,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks</emphasis>
. Described from one or more females from: Umballa (ZSI). A female 
<typeStatus box="[1143,1194,1350,1376]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,256,1389,1415]" name="Pakistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, was figured by Distant (
<number box="[562,625,1389,1415]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1908.0">1908</number>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Morrison" box="[693,897,1389,1415]" pageId="11" pageNumber="21" refString="Morrison, W. P. (1973) A revision of the Hecalinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) of the oriental region. Pacific Insects, 15 (3 - 4), 379 - 438." type="journal article" year="1973">
Morrison (
<number box="[823,888,1389,1415]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1973.0">1973</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Subsequently, Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan (
<number box="[1365,1428,1389,1415]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1990.0">1990</number>
) figured a male from 
<collectingCountry box="[403,469,1428,1454]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">India</collectingCountry>
. The latter identification could be correct as the authors mentioned the unusual longitudinal yellow bands on the vertex and pronotum, although they did not mention the distinctive spatulate head which is also present in the 
<typeStatus box="[538,592,1505,1531]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
. Their figure of the aedeagus matches the unnamed figure by Mahmood (
<number box="[159,221,1544,1570]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1979.0">1979</number>
, code CP 
<number box="[334,363,1544,1570]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="59.0">59</number>
) but the description of this species (p. 
<number box="[806,839,1544,1570]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="47.0">47</number>
) makes no mention of the bands.
</paragraph>
